{"title": "The Ruined Garden", "text": "The Ruined Garden  My childhood was only a menacing shower, cut now and ten by hours of brilliant heat. All the top soil was killed by rain and sleet, my garden hardly bore a standing flower.  From now on, my mind's autumn! I must take the field and dress my beds with spade and rake and restore order to my flooded grounds. There the rain raised mountains like burial mounds.  I throw fresh seeds out. Who knows what survives? What elements will give us life and food? This soil is irrigated by the tides.  Time and nature sluice away our lives. A virus eats the heart out of our sides, digs in and multiplies on our lost blood. ", "nonempty_line_count": 14, "stanza_count": 4, "stanza_structure": [4, 4, 3, 3], "total_syllables": 148, "syllables_per_line": 10.571, "poem_word_frequencies_hash": {"THE": 6, "RUINED": 1, "GARDEN": 2, "": 5, "MY": 5, "CHILDHOOD": 1, "WAS": 2, "ONLY": 1, "A": 3, "MENACING": 1, "SHOWER": 1, "CUT": 1, "NOW": 2, "AND": 8, "TEN": 1, "BY": 3, "HOURS": 1, "OF": 2, "BRILLIANT": 1, "HEAT": 1, "ALL": 1, "TOP": 1, "SOIL": 2, "KILLED": 1, "RAIN": 2, "SLEET": 1, "HARDLY": 1, "BORE": 1, "STANDING": 1, "FLOWER": 1, "FROM": 1, "ON": 2, "MIND'S": 1, "AUTUMN": 1, "I": 2, "MUST": 1, "TAKE": 1, "FIELD": 1, "DRESS": 1, "BEDS": 1, "WITH": 1, "SPADE": 1, "RAKE": 1, "RESTORE": 1, "ORDER": 1, "TO": 1, "FLOODED": 1, "GROUNDS": 1, "THERE": 1, "RAISED": 1, "MOUNTAINS": 1, "LIKE": 1, "BURIAL": 1, "MOUNDS": 1, "THROW": 1, "FRESH": 1, "SEEDS": 1, "OUT": 2, "WHO": 1, "KNOWS": 1, "WHAT": 2, "SURVIVES": 1, "ELEMENTS": 1, "WILL": 1, "GIVE": 1, "US": 1, "LIFE": 1, "FOOD": 1, "THIS": 1, "IS": 1, "IRRIGATED": 1, "TIDES": 1, "TIME": 1, "NATURE": 1, "SLUICE": 1, "AWAY": 1, "OUR": 3, "LIVES": 1, "VIRUS": 1, "EATS": 1, "HEART": 1, "SIDES": 1, "DIGS": 1, "IN": 1, "MULTIPLIES": 1, "LOST": 1, "BLOOD": 1}, "sig": "", "length_letters_only": 492, "linelist": [{"text": "The Ruined Garden", "syllable_list": [1, 2, 2], "syllable_count": 5, "letters_only": 